{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require stricter standards for Type 1 diabetes support in schools",
        "additional_details": "Families across the UK report children with Type 1 diabetes being left without safe support in school. Evidence from tribunals, charities and parliamentary submissions shows care plans are often not followed, that schools rely on a single trained member of staff, that parents are expected to attend school, and that children sometimes miss education due to unsafe provision. A child\u2019s safety should not depend on their postcode or individual school decisions.",
        "background": "Introduce stricter, enforceable, national standards for supporting pupils with Type 1 diabetes in schools. Including mandatory training for sufficient staff to cover the school day, more consistent implementation of healthcare plans, and clearer accountability when support fails.",
